      "writtenOn": "2020-04-02T21:59:02Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Nobody can be sure whether this is an arch-specific thing or an OS-specific thing, so how about:\n\n#if defined(ARCH_CPU_X86_64) \u0026\u0026 TARGET_OS_SIMULATOR\n  // one thing\n#elif defined(ARCH_CPU_ARM64) \u0026\u0026 !TARGET_OS_SIMULATOR\n  // other thing\n#else\n#error Port\n#endif\n\nNote that even if we didn’t need to add the TARGET_OS_SIMULATOR bit, the #error would be an excellent idea, because this won’t otherwise break the compilation when porting to a new architecture, although libdispatch will almost certainly need to be added to the list. You might have a test that catches this, but a compile-time error is even better.",
      "range": {
