      "writtenOn": "2020-04-02T21:59:02Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I’m not sold on LOG(FATAL) as the best way to exit in this situation. We should match the genuine uncaught exception behavior so that the way that this is reported after our own handling appears to other tools as close to what’s expected for an uncaught exception as possible. “Other tools” include a debugger, the system’s crash reporter, and even the exit status reported via waitpid.\n\nIn general, I think that favors an exit via std::terminate (and it’s worth a comment saying why).",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 109,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 110,
        "endChar": 47
      },
      "revId": "bbdc8f8d02f4214e63c6bb0636364530159b3083",
