      "message": "\u003e I do, on Simulator library path will be something awful like:\n\u003e \n\u003e \"/Applications/Xcode.app/Contents/Developer/Platforms/iPhoneOS.platform/Library/Developer/CoreSimulator/Profiles/Runtimes/iOS.simruntime/Contents/Resources/RuntimeRoot/usr/lib/system/introspection/libdispatch.dylib\"\n\nGot it. That’s the sort of detail that’s worth mentioning in a comment! Nobody’s going to know what sort of input this thing is going to have to deal with unless you write it down. People are going to assume that since what you have looks like a normal path, it’s really just a normal path…\n\nThese crazy paths are only relevant to the simulator, so I think we should do a straight equality comparison on devices, and do something else where you have crazy paths.\n\nAnd it seems like you don’t really want a substring search, you just want to see if the library path ends with the string you’re looking for.",
